{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ENZ2VhQ7Nu9xvgVvhdgkvx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully read all Java source files and the requested configuration files. Here is the complete summary:\n\n## Complete File Contents\n\nI have read all 100 Java source files in the directory along with the configuration files. Below is the breakdown:\n\n### Configuration Files:\n\n1. **import.sql** (/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/import.sql)\n   - Contains a single SQL statement to insert into ApplicationSettings table\n\n2. **web.xml** (/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/web.xml)\n   - Jakarta Faces configuration with PrimeFaces settings\n   - Servlet mappings for Faces Servlet\n   - MIME type mappings for fonts\n\n3. **faces-config.xml** (/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/resources/META-INF/faces-config.xml)\n   - PrimeFaces dialog configuration\n\n### Java Source Files (100 files total):\n\nThe Java files are organized into the following packages:\n\n**Application Layer:**\n- HandlingEventService.java\n- BookingService.java\n- CargoInspectionService.java\n- ApplicationEvents.java\n- Internal implementations (DefaultHandlingEventService, DefaultBookingService, DefaultCargoInspectionService)\n- Utilities (InitLoader, ApplicationSettings, DateConverter, SampleDataGenerator, RestConfiguration)\n\n**Domain Model:**\n- **Cargo:** Cargo, CargoRepository, TrackingId, Itinerary, Leg, Delivery, HandlingActivity, RouteSpecification, TransportStatus, RoutingStatus\n- **Handling:** HandlingEvent, HandlingEventFactory, HandlingEventRepository, HandlingHistory, CannotCreateHandlingEventException, UnknownCargoException, UnknownLocationException, UnknownVoyageException\n- **Location:** Location, LocationRepository, UnLocode, SampleLocations\n- **Voyage:** Voyage, VoyageNumber, VoyageRepository, Schedule, CarrierMovement, SampleVoyages\n- **Shared:** Specification, AbstractSpecification, AndSpecification, OrSpecification, NotSpecification, DomainObjectUtils\n\n**Domain Services:**\n- RoutingService\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- **Persistence (JPA):** JpaCargoRepository, JpaHandlingEventRepository, JpaLocationRepository, JpaVoyageRepository\n- **Messaging (JMS):** JmsApplicationEvents, CargoHandledConsumer, DeliveredCargoConsumer, MisdirectedCargoConsumer, RejectedRegistrationAttemptsConsumer, HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptConsumer\n- **Routing:** ExternalRoutingService\n- **Logging:** LoggerProducer\n- **Events:** CargoUpdated (CDI qualifier)\n\n**Interfaces Layer:**\n- **Configuration:** FacesConfiguration, CoordinatesFactory, Coordinates\n- **Booking Facade:** BookingServiceFacade, DefaultBookingServiceFacade\n- **DTOs:** CargoRoute, CargoStatus, Location, Leg, RouteCandidate, TrackingEvents\n- **Assemblers:** CargoRouteDtoAssembler, CargoStatusDtoAssembler, ItineraryCandidateDtoAssembler, LocationDtoAssembler, TrackingEventsDtoAssembler\n- **Web (Booking):** Booking, ListCargo, CargoDetails, Track, ItinerarySelection, ChangeDestination, ChangeDestinationDialog, ChangeArrivalDeadline, ChangeArrivalDeadlineDialog\n- **Web (Tracking):** Track, CargoTrackingViewAdapter\n- **SSE:** RealtimeCargoTrackingService, RealtimeCargoTrackingViewAdapter, LocationViewAdapter\n- **Handling:** HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt\n- **File Processing:** EventItemReader, EventItemWriter, EventFilesCheckpoint, EventLineParseException\n\n**Pathfinder (Graph Traversal Service):**\n- GraphTraversalService\n- TransitPath, TransitPaths, TransitEdge\n- GraphDao (internal)\n\nAll files have been read in their entirety. This is a Quarkus-based cargo tracking application following Domain-Driven Design principles, with Jakarta EE technologies (CDI, JPA, JMS, Jakarta Faces, JAX-RS), PrimeFaces for the UI, and batch processing capabilities."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"874c3bc6-51ef-4df2-a3c2-47035449d133"}
