{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DxBGASmof5rHdrryTbgtYU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01MfAb5zsgzq1RX2Frc4QYma","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__cargotracker__quarkus__spring/run_3/output/src/main/java/org/eclipse/cargotracker/interfaces/booking/web/ListCargo.java"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8130,"cache_read_input_tokens":62882,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8130,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":782},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"21ac9889-d911-4d20-872c-a8f63221e5f2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019WT9fc222kciS8dW1kcaXs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Embedded;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingHistory;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * A Cargo. This is the central class in the domain model, and it is the root of the\n    20→ * Cargo-Itinerary-Leg-Delivery-RouteSpecification aggregate.\n    21→ *\n    22→ * <p>\n    23→ * A cargo is identified by a unique tracking ID, and it always has an origin and a route\n    24→ * specification. The life cycle of a cargo begins with the booking procedure, when the tracking ID\n    25→ * is assigned. During a (short) period of time, between booking and initial routing, the cargo has\n    26→ * no itinerary.\n    27→ *\n    28→ * <p>\n    29→ * The booking clerk requests a list of possible routes, matching the route specification, and\n    30→ * assigns the cargo to one route. The route to which a cargo is assigned is described by an\n    31→ * itinerary.\n    32→ *\n    33→ * <p>\n    34→ * A cargo can be re-routed during transport, on demand of the customer, in which case a new route\n    35→ * is specified for the cargo and a new route is requested. The old itinerary, being a value object,\n    36→ * is discarded and a new one is attached.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * <p>\n    39→ * It may also happen that a cargo is accidentally misrouted, which should notify the proper\n    40→ * personnel and also trigger a re-routing procedure.\n    41→ *\n    42→ * <p>\n    43→ * When a cargo is handled, the status of the delivery changes. Everything about the delivery of the\n    44→ * cargo is contained in the Delivery value object, which is replaced whenever a cargo is handled by\n    45→ * an asynchronous event triggered by the registration of the handling event.\n    46→ *\n    47→ * <p>\n    48→ * The delivery can also be affected by routing changes, i.e. when a the route specification\n    49→ * changes, or the cargo is assigned to a new route. In that case, the delivery update is performed\n    50→ * synchronously within the cargo aggregate.\n    51→ *\n    52→ * <p>\n    53→ * The life cycle of a cargo ends when the cargo is claimed by the customer.\n    54→ *\n    55→ * <p>\n    56→ * The cargo aggregate, and the entire domain model, is built to solve the problem of booking and\n    57→ * tracking cargo. All important business rules for determining whether or not a cargo is\n    58→ * misdirected, what the current status of the cargo is (on board carrier, in port etc), are\n    59→ * captured in this aggregate.\n    60→ */\n    61→@Entity\n    62→@NamedQuery(\n    63→    name = \"Cargo.findByTrackingId\",\n    64→    query = \"Select c from Cargo c where c.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    65→public class Cargo implements Serializable {\n    66→\n    67→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    68→\n    69→  @Id\n    70→  @GeneratedValue\n    71→  private Long id;\n    72→\n    73→  @Embedded\n    74→  @NotNull(message = \"Tracking ID is required.\")\n    75→  private TrackingId trackingId;\n    76→\n    77→  @ManyToOne\n    78→  @JoinColumn(name = \"origin_id\", updatable = false)\n    79→  @NotNull\n    80→  private Location origin;\n    81→\n    82→  @Embedded\n    83→  @NotNull(message = \"Route specification is required.\")\n    84→  private RouteSpecification routeSpecification;\n    85→\n    86→  @Embedded\n    87→  @NotNull\n    88→  private Itinerary itinerary;\n    89→  @Embedded\n    90→  @NotNull\n    91→  private Delivery delivery;\n    92→\n    93→  public Cargo() {\n    94→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  public Cargo(TrackingId trackingId, RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n    98→    Validate.notNull(trackingId, \"Tracking ID is required.\");\n    99→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n   100→\n   101→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n   102→    // Cargo origin never changes, even if the route specification changes.\n   103→    // However, at creation, cargo origin can be derived from the initial\n   104→    // route specification.\n   105→    this.origin = routeSpecification.getOrigin();\n   106→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n   107→\n   108→    this.delivery =\n   109→        Delivery.derivedFrom(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary, HandlingHistory.EMPTY);\n   110→    this.itinerary = Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY;\n   111→  }\n   112→\n   113→  public TrackingId getTrackingId() {\n   114→    return trackingId;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  public Location getOrigin() {\n   118→    return origin;\n   119→  }\n   120→\n   121→  public void setOrigin(Location origin) {\n   122→    this.origin = origin;\n   123→  }\n   124→\n   125→  public RouteSpecification getRouteSpecification() {\n   126→    return routeSpecification;\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  /** @return The delivery. Never null. */\n   130→  public Delivery getDelivery() {\n   131→    return delivery;\n   132→  }\n   133→\n   134→  /** @return The itinerary. Never null. */\n   135→  public Itinerary getItinerary() {\n   136→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.itinerary, Itinerary.EMPTY_ITINERARY);\n   137→  }\n   138→\n   139→  /** Specifies a new route for this cargo. */\n   140→  public void specifyNewRoute(RouteSpecification routeSpecification) {\n   141→    Validate.notNull(routeSpecification, \"Route specification is required.\");\n   142→\n   143→    this.routeSpecification = routeSpecification;\n   144→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   145→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   146→  }\n   147→\n   148→  public void assignToRoute(Itinerary itinerary) {\n   149→    Validate.notNull(itinerary, \"Itinerary is required for assignment.\");\n   150→\n   151→    this.itinerary = itinerary;\n   152→    // Handling consistency within the Cargo aggregate synchronously\n   153→    this.delivery = delivery.updateOnRouting(this.routeSpecification, this.itinerary);\n   154→  }\n   155→\n   156→  /**\n   157→   * Updates all aspects of the cargo aggregate status based on the current route specification,\n   158→   * itinerary and handling of the cargo.\n   159→   *\n   160→   * <p>\n   161→   * When either of those three changes, i.e. when a new route is specified for the cargo, the cargo\n   162→   * is assigned to a route or when the cargo is handled, the status must be re-calculated.\n   163→   *\n   164→   * <p>\n   165→   * {@link RouteSpecification} and {@link Itinerary} are both inside the Cargo aggregate, so\n   166→   * changes to them cause the status to be updated <b>synchronously</b>, but changes to the\n   167→   * delivery history (when a cargo is handled) cause the status update to happen\n   168→   * <b>asynchronously</b> since {@link HandlingEvent} is in a different aggregate.\n   169→   *\n   170→   * @param handlingHistory handling history\n   171→   */\n   172→  public void deriveDeliveryProgress(HandlingHistory handlingHistory) {\n   173→    this.delivery = Delivery.derivedFrom(getRouteSpecification(), getItinerary(), handlingHistory);\n   174→  }\n   175→\n   176→  /**\n   177→   * @param object to compare\n   178→   * @return True if they have the same identity\n   179→   * @see #sameIdentityAs(Cargo)\n   180→   */\n   181→  @Override\n   182→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n   183→    if (this == object) {\n   184→      return true;\n   185→    }\n   186→    if (object == null || !(object instanceof Cargo)) {\n   187→      return false;\n   188→    }\n   189→\n   190→    Cargo other = (Cargo) object;\n   191→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n   192→  }\n   193→\n   194→  private boolean sameIdentityAs(Cargo other) {\n   195→    return other != null && trackingId.sameValueAs(other.trackingId);\n   196→  }\n   197→\n   198→  /** @return Hash code of tracking id. */\n   199→  @Override\n   200→  public int hashCode() {\n   201→    return trackingId.hashCode();\n   202→  }\n   203→\n   204→  @Override\n   205→  public String toString() {\n   206→    return trackingId.toString();\n   207→  }\n   208→}\n   209→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"8dcab8e3-61f1-4191-9741-91800940e7b5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KSgoi65tjUgJXTx7NoRxW3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.EnumType;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Enumerated;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    13→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    15→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    16→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    17→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    18→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.EqualsBuilder;\n    19→import org.apache.commons.lang3.builder.HashCodeBuilder;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.shared.DomainObjectUtils;\n    25→\n    26→/**\n    27→ * A HandlingEvent is used to register the event when, for instance, a cargo is unloaded from a\n    28→ * carrier at a some location at a given time.\n    29→ *\n    30→ * <p>\n    31→ * The HandlingEvent's are sent from different Incident Logging Applications some time after the\n    32→ * event occurred and contain information about the null {@link TrackingId}, {@link Location}, time\n    33→ * stamp of the completion of the event, and possibly, if applicable a {@link Voyage}.\n    34→ *\n    35→ * <p>\n    36→ * This class is the only member, and consequently the root, of the HandlingEvent aggregate.\n    37→ *\n    38→ * <p>\n    39→ * HandlingEvent's could contain information about a {@link Voyage} and if so, the event type must\n    40→ * be either {@link Type#LOAD} or {@link Type#UNLOAD}.\n    41→ *\n    42→ * <p>\n    43→ * All other events must be of {@link Type#RECEIVE}, {@link Type#CLAIM} or {@link Type#CUSTOMS}.\n    44→ */\n    45→@Entity\n    46→@NamedQuery(\n    47→    name = \"HandlingEvent.findByTrackingId\",\n    48→    query = \"Select e from HandlingEvent e where e.cargo.trackingId = :trackingId\")\n    49→public class HandlingEvent implements Serializable {\n    50→\n    51→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    52→\n    53→  @Id\n    54→  @GeneratedValue\n    55→  private Long id;\n    56→\n    57→  @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)\n    58→  @NotNull\n    59→  private Type type;\n    60→\n    61→  @ManyToOne\n    62→  @JoinColumn(name = \"voyage_id\")\n    63→  private Voyage voyage;\n    64→\n    65→  @ManyToOne\n    66→  @JoinColumn(name = \"location_id\")\n    67→  @NotNull\n    68→  private Location location;\n    69→\n    70→  @NotNull\n    71→  @Column(name = \"completionTime\")\n    72→  private LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    73→\n    74→  @NotNull\n    75→  @Column(name = \"registration\")\n    76→  private LocalDateTime registrationTime;\n    77→\n    78→  @ManyToOne\n    79→  @JoinColumn(name = \"cargo_id\")\n    80→  @NotNull\n    81→  private Cargo cargo;\n    82→\n    83→  @Transient\n    84→  private String summary;\n    85→\n    86→  public HandlingEvent() {\n    87→    // Nothing to initialize.\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  /**\n    91→   * @param cargo The cargo\n    92→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n    93→   *        the receive took place).\n    94→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n    95→   * @param type type of event\n    96→   * @param location where the event took place\n    97→   * @param voyage the voyage\n    98→   */\n    99→  public HandlingEvent(\n   100→      Cargo cargo,\n   101→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n   102→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n   103→      Type type,\n   104→      Location location,\n   105→      Voyage voyage) {\n   106→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   107→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   108→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   109→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   110→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   111→    Validate.notNull(voyage, \"Voyage is required\");\n   112→\n   113→    if (type.prohibitsVoyage()) {\n   114→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is not allowed with event type \" + type);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    this.voyage = voyage;\n   118→\n   119→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   120→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   121→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   122→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   123→    this.type = type;\n   124→    this.location = location;\n   125→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   126→  }\n   127→\n   128→  /**\n   129→   * @param cargo cargo\n   130→   * @param completionTime completion time, the reported time that the event actually happened (e.g.\n   131→   *        the receive took place).\n   132→   * @param registrationTime registration time, the time the message is received\n   133→   * @param type type of event\n   134→   * @param location where the event took place\n   135→   */\n   136→  public HandlingEvent(\n   137→      Cargo cargo,\n   138→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n   139→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n   140→      Type type,\n   141→      Location location) {\n   142→    Validate.notNull(cargo, \"Cargo is required\");\n   143→    Validate.notNull(completionTime, \"Completion time is required\");\n   144→    Validate.notNull(registrationTime, \"Registration time is required\");\n   145→    Validate.notNull(type, \"Handling event type is required\");\n   146→    Validate.notNull(location, \"Location is required\");\n   147→\n   148→    if (type.requiresVoyage()) {\n   149→      throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Voyage is required for event type \" + type);\n   150→    }\n   151→\n   152→    // This is a workaround to a Hibernate issue. when the `LocalDateTime` field is persisted into\n   153→    // the DB, and retrieved from the DB, the values are different by nanoseconds.\n   154→    this.completionTime = completionTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   155→    this.registrationTime = registrationTime.truncatedTo(ChronoUnit.SECONDS);\n   156→    this.type = type;\n   157→    this.location = location;\n   158→    this.cargo = cargo;\n   159→    this.voyage = null;\n   160→  }\n   161→\n   162→  public Type getType() {\n   163→    return this.type;\n   164→  }\n   165→\n   166→  public Voyage getVoyage() {\n   167→    return DomainObjectUtils.nullSafe(this.voyage, Voyage.NONE);\n   168→  }\n   169→\n   170→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n   171→    return completionTime;\n   172→  }\n   173→\n   174→  public LocalDateTime getRegistrationTime() {\n   175→    return registrationTime;\n   176→  }\n   177→\n   178→  public Location getLocation() {\n   179→    return this.location;\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  public Cargo getCargo() {\n   183→    return this.cargo;\n   184→  }\n   185→\n   186→  public String getSummary() {\n   187→    StringBuilder builder =\n   188→        new StringBuilder(location.getName())\n   189→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   190→            .append(completionTime)\n   191→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   192→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   193→            .append(type)\n   194→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   195→            .append(\"Reg.: \")\n   196→            .append(registrationTime)\n   197→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   198→\n   199→    if (voyage != null) {\n   200→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber());\n   201→    }\n   202→\n   203→    return builder.toString();\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→  @Override\n   207→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   208→    if (this == o) {\n   209→      return true;\n   210→    }\n   211→\n   212→    if (o == null || !(o instanceof HandlingEvent)) {\n   213→      return false;\n   214→    }\n   215→\n   216→    HandlingEvent event = (HandlingEvent) o;\n   217→\n   218→    return sameEventAs(event);\n   219→  }\n   220→\n   221→  private boolean sameEventAs(HandlingEvent other) {\n   222→    return other != null\n   223→        && new EqualsBuilder()\n   224→            .append(this.cargo, other.cargo)\n   225→            .append(this.voyage, other.voyage)\n   226→            .append(this.completionTime, other.completionTime)\n   227→            .append(this.location, other.location)\n   228→            .append(this.type, other.type)\n   229→            .isEquals();\n   230→  }\n   231→\n   232→  @Override\n   233→  public int hashCode() {\n   234→    return new HashCodeBuilder()\n   235→        .append(cargo)\n   236→        .append(voyage)\n   237→        .append(completionTime)\n   238→        .append(location)\n   239→        .append(type)\n   240→        .toHashCode();\n   241→  }\n   242→\n   243→  @Override\n   244→  public String toString() {\n   245→    StringBuilder builder =\n   246→        new StringBuilder(\"\\n--- Handling event ---\\n\")\n   247→            .append(\"Cargo: \")\n   248→            .append(cargo.getTrackingId())\n   249→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   250→            .append(\"Type: \")\n   251→            .append(type)\n   252→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   253→            .append(\"Location: \")\n   254→            .append(location.getName())\n   255→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   256→            .append(\"Completed on: \")\n   257→            .append(completionTime)\n   258→            .append(\"\\n\")\n   259→            .append(\"Registered on: \")\n   260→            .append(registrationTime)\n   261→            .append(\"\\n\");\n   262→\n   263→    if (voyage != null) {\n   264→      builder.append(\"Voyage: \").append(voyage.getVoyageNumber()).append(\"\\n\");\n   265→    }\n   266→\n   267→    return builder.toString();\n   268→  }\n   269→\n   270→  /**\n   271→   * Handling event type. Either requires or prohibits a carrier movement association, it's never\n   272→   * optional.\n   273→   */\n   274→  public enum Type {\n   275→\n   276→    // Loaded onto voyage from port location.\n   277→    LOAD(true),\n   278→    // Unloaded from voyage to port location\n   279→    UNLOAD(true),\n   280→    // Received by carrier\n   281→    RECEIVE(false),\n   282→    // Cargo claimed by recepient\n   283→    CLAIM(false),\n   284→    // Cargo went through customs\n   285→    CUSTOMS(false);\n   286→\n   287→    private final boolean voyageRequired;\n   288→\n   289→    /**\n   290→     * Private enum constructor.\n   291→     *\n   292→     * @param voyageRequired whether or not a voyage is associated with this event type\n   293→     */\n   294→    private Type(boolean voyageRequired) {\n   295→      this.voyageRequired = voyageRequired;\n   296→    }\n   297→\n   298→    /** @return True if a voyage association is required for this event type. */\n   299→    public boolean requiresVoyage() {\n   300→      return voyageRequired;\n   301→    }\n   302→\n   303→    /** @return True if a voyage association is prohibited for this event type. */\n   304→    public boolean prohibitsVoyage() {\n   305→      return !requiresVoyage();\n   306→    }\n   307→\n   308→    public boolean sameValueAs(Type other) {\n   309→      return other != null && this.equals(other);\n   310→    }\n   311→  }\n   312→}\n   313→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"f7e80613-cfcc-4f46-81e7-1d9a129054a8"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VnYoy64XnZ4m8hQYMqmLXe","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.LocationRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageRepository;\n    17→\n    18→@ApplicationScoped\n    19→public class HandlingEventFactory implements Serializable {\n    20→\n    21→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    22→\n    23→  @Inject\n    24→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    25→  @Inject\n    26→  private VoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    27→  @Inject\n    28→  private LocationRepository locationRepository;\n    29→\n    30→  /**\n    31→   * @param registrationTime time when this event was received by the system\n    32→   * @param completionTime when the event was completed, for example finished loading\n    33→   * @param trackingId cargo tracking id\n    34→   * @param voyageNumber voyage number\n    35→   * @param unlocode United Nations Location Code for the location of the event\n    36→   * @param type type of event\n    37→   * @return A handling event.\n    38→   * @throws UnknownVoyageException if there's no voyage with this number\n    39→   * @throws UnknownCargoException if there's no cargo with this tracking id\n    40→   * @throws UnknownLocationException if there's no location with this UN Locode\n    41→   */\n    42→  // TODO [Clean Code] Look at the exception handling more seriously.\n    43→  @Transactional(rollbackOn = CannotCreateHandlingEventException.class) // to match the old behavior\n    44→  public HandlingEvent createHandlingEvent(\n    45→      LocalDateTime registrationTime,\n    46→      LocalDateTime completionTime,\n    47→      TrackingId trackingId,\n    48→      VoyageNumber voyageNumber,\n    49→      UnLocode unlocode,\n    50→      HandlingEvent.Type type)\n    51→      throws CannotCreateHandlingEventException {\n    52→    Cargo cargo = findCargo(trackingId);\n    53→    Voyage voyage = findVoyage(voyageNumber);\n    54→    Location location = findLocation(unlocode);\n    55→\n    56→    try {\n    57→      if (voyage == null) {\n    58→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location);\n    59→      } else {\n    60→        return new HandlingEvent(cargo, completionTime, registrationTime, type, location, voyage);\n    61→      }\n    62→    } catch (Exception e) {\n    63→      throw new CannotCreateHandlingEventException(e);\n    64→    }\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  private Cargo findCargo(TrackingId trackingId) throws UnknownCargoException {\n    68→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(trackingId);\n    69→\n    70→    if (cargo == null) {\n    71→      throw new UnknownCargoException(trackingId);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    return cargo;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  private Voyage findVoyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber) throws UnknownVoyageException {\n    78→    if (voyageNumber == null) {\n    79→      return null;\n    80→    }\n    81→\n    82→    Voyage voyage = voyageRepository.find(voyageNumber);\n    83→\n    84→    if (voyage == null) {\n    85→      throw new UnknownVoyageException(voyageNumber);\n    86→    }\n    87→\n    88→    return voyage;\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  private Location findLocation(UnLocode unlocode) throws UnknownLocationException {\n    92→    Location location = locationRepository.find(unlocode);\n    93→\n    94→    if (location == null) {\n    95→      throw new UnknownLocationException(unlocode);\n    96→    }\n    97→\n    98→    return location;\n    99→  }\n   100→}\n   101→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"2f4a4e61-8176-468f-9120-a693000d5105"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_019oVoUto7wBvC3GLaicZ26w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.Objects;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Embedded;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * A location in our model is stops on a journey, such as cargo origin or destination, or carrier\n    15→ * movement end points.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>\n    18→ * It is uniquely identified by a UN location code.\n    19→ */\n    20→@Entity\n    21→@NamedQuery(\n    22→    name = \"Location.findByUnLocode\",\n    23→    query = \"Select l from Location l where l.unLocode = :unLocode\")\n    24→public class Location implements Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    27→\n    28→  // Special Location object that marks an unknown location.\n    29→  public static final Location UNKNOWN = new Location(new UnLocode(\"XXXXX\"), \"Unknown location\");\n    30→\n    31→  @Id\n    32→  @GeneratedValue\n    33→  private Long id;\n    34→  @Embedded\n    35→  @NotNull\n    36→  private UnLocode unLocode;\n    37→  @NotEmpty\n    38→  private String name;\n    39→\n    40→  public Location() {\n    41→    // Nothing to do.\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  /**\n    45→   * @param unLocode UN Locode\n    46→   * @param name Location name\n    47→   * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the UN Locode or name is null\n    48→   */\n    49→  public Location(UnLocode unLocode, String name) {\n    50→    Objects.requireNonNull(unLocode);\n    51→    Objects.requireNonNull(name);\n    52→\n    53→    this.unLocode = unLocode;\n    54→    this.name = name;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  /** @return UN location code for this location. */\n    58→  public UnLocode getUnLocode() {\n    59→    return unLocode;\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  /** @return Actual name of this location, e.g. \"Stockholm\". */\n    63→  public String getName() {\n    64→    return name;\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  /**\n    68→   * @param object to compare\n    69→   * @return Since this is an entiy this will be true iff UN locodes are equal.\n    70→   */\n    71→  @Override\n    72→  public boolean equals(Object object) {\n    73→    if (object == null) {\n    74→      return false;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    if (this == object) {\n    78→      return true;\n    79→    }\n    80→\n    81→    if (!(object instanceof Location)) {\n    82→      return false;\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    Location other = (Location) object;\n    86→\n    87→    return sameIdentityAs(other);\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Location other) {\n    91→    return this.unLocode.sameValueAs(other.unLocode);\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  /** @return Hash code of UN locode. */\n    95→  @Override\n    96→  public int hashCode() {\n    97→    return unLocode.hashCode();\n    98→  }\n    99→\n   100→  @Override\n   101→  public String toString() {\n   102→    return name + \" [\" + unLocode + \"]\";\n   103→  }\n   104→}\n   105→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"27cde08a-fc5f-4174-9812-dc377063cba3"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013ixp5N3AB6rnbJJrHa2tiQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Embedded;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.GeneratedValue;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.Id;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.NamedQuery;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n    13→import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    15→\n    16→@Entity\n    17→@NamedQuery(\n    18→    name = \"Voyage.findByVoyageNumber\",\n    19→    query = \"Select v from Voyage v where v.voyageNumber = :voyageNumber\")\n    20→public class Voyage implements Serializable {\n    21→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    22→\n    23→  // Null object pattern\n    24→  public static final Voyage NONE = new Voyage(new VoyageNumber(\"\"), Schedule.EMPTY);\n    25→\n    26→  @Id\n    27→  @GeneratedValue\n    28→  private Long id;\n    29→\n    30→  @Embedded\n    31→  @NotNull(message = \"Voyage number is required.\")\n    32→  private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    33→\n    34→  @Embedded\n    35→  @NotNull(message = \"Schedule is required.\")\n    36→  private Schedule schedule;\n    37→\n    38→  public Voyage() {\n    39→    // Nothing to initialize\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public Voyage(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Schedule schedule) {\n    43→    Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required.\");\n    44→    Validate.notNull(schedule, \"Schedule is required.\");\n    45→\n    46→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n    47→    this.schedule = schedule;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public VoyageNumber getVoyageNumber() {\n    51→    return voyageNumber;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public Schedule getSchedule() {\n    55→    return schedule;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  @Override\n    59→  public int hashCode() {\n    60→    return voyageNumber.hashCode();\n    61→  }\n    62→\n    63→  @Override\n    64→  public boolean equals(Object o) {\n    65→    if (this == o) {\n    66→      return true;\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    if (o == null) {\n    70→      return false;\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    if (!(o instanceof Voyage)) {\n    74→      return false;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    Voyage that = (Voyage) o;\n    78→\n    79→    return sameIdentityAs(that);\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public boolean sameIdentityAs(Voyage other) {\n    83→    return other != null && this.getVoyageNumber().sameValueAs(other.getVoyageNumber());\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  @Override\n    87→  public String toString() {\n    88→    return \"Voyage \" + voyageNumber;\n    89→  }\n    90→\n    91→  /**\n    92→   * Builder pattern is used for incremental construction of a Voyage aggregate. This serves as an\n    93→   * aggregate factory.\n    94→   */\n    95→  public static class Builder {\n    96→\n    97→    private List<CarrierMovement> carrierMovements = new ArrayList<>();\n    98→    private VoyageNumber voyageNumber;\n    99→    private Location departureLocation;\n   100→\n   101→    public Builder(VoyageNumber voyageNumber, Location departureLocation) {\n   102→      Validate.notNull(voyageNumber, \"Voyage number is required\");\n   103→      Validate.notNull(departureLocation, \"Departure location is required\");\n   104→\n   105→      this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n   106→      this.departureLocation = departureLocation;\n   107→    }\n   108→\n   109→    public Builder addMovement(\n   110→        Location arrivalLocation, LocalDateTime departureTime, LocalDateTime arrivalTime) {\n   111→      carrierMovements.add(\n   112→          new CarrierMovement(departureLocation, arrivalLocation, departureTime, arrivalTime));\n   113→\n   114→      // Next departure location is the same as this arrival location\n   115→      this.departureLocation = arrivalLocation;\n   116→\n   117→      return this;\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    public Voyage build() {\n   121→      return new Voyage(voyageNumber, new Schedule(carrierMovements));\n   122→    }\n   123→  }\n   124→}\n   125→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"3289f8cc-9f80-462a-9aa0-1650b532b27b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VheYQD4Dk5ko4BNiJbviRd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→INSERT INTO ApplicationSettings (id, sampleLoaded) VALUES (1, FALSE);\n     2→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"59377d78-56a9-46e1-9432-cc73036d831f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MfAb5zsgzq1RX2Frc4QYma","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toList;\n     4→\n     5→import java.util.List;\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles listing cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    15→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    16→ * interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>\n    19→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    20→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    21→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    22→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@RequestScoped\n    26→public class ListCargo {\n    27→\n    28→  @Inject\n    29→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    30→\n    31→  private List<CargoRoute> notRoutedCargos;\n    32→  private List<CargoRoute> routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    33→  private List<CargoRoute> claimedCargos;\n    34→\n    35→  @PostConstruct\n    36→  public void init() {\n    37→    List<CargoRoute> cargos = bookingServiceFacade.listAllCargos();\n    38→    notRoutedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(route -> !route.isRouted()).collect(toList());\n    39→    routedUnclaimedCargos =\n    40→        cargos.stream().filter(route -> route.isRouted() && !route.isClaimed()).collect(toList());\n    41→    claimedCargos = cargos.stream().filter(CargoRoute::isClaimed).collect(toList());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public List<CargoRoute> getNotRoutedCargos() {\n    45→    return notRoutedCargos;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public List<CargoRoute> getRoutedUnclaimedCargos() {\n    49→    return routedUnclaimedCargos;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  public List<CargoRoute> getClaimedCargos() {\n    53→    return claimedCargos;\n    54→  }\n    55→}\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"b7b03a26-a38a-40e0-b8b1-a7abdd16450f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01Dp4N8E4MHHwKgYbHpaRfsQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. This is a complex DDD-based Cargo Tracker application using Quarkus with:\n\n1. **Quarkus Panache** repositories (must replace with Spring Data JPA / EntityManager)\n2. **CDI** (`@ApplicationScoped`, `@Inject`, `@Produces`, CDI events) -> Spring (`@Service`, `@Component`, `@Autowired`, Spring events)\n3. **JMS messaging** with AMQP/Qpid -> Replace with Spring JMS + embedded broker or Spring events\n4. **JAX-RS REST endpoints** (`@Path`, `@GET`, `@POST`) -> Spring Web (`@RestController`, `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`)\n5. **Jakarta Faces (JSF/PrimeFaces)** web UI -> Replace with Thymeleaf or keep JSF via JoinFaces\n6. **Quarkus-specific** annotations (`@Startup`, `@UnlessBuildProfile`, Quarkus lifecycle events)\n7. **MicroProfile Config** (`@ConfigProperty`) -> Spring (`@Value`)\n8. **SSE (Server-Sent Events)** with JAX-RS -> Spring SseEmitter\n\nGiven the massive complexity, the best strategy is to replace the JSF-based UI with Spring MVC + REST controllers, remove JSF, keep JPA with Spring Data, replace JMS with Spring's built-in async event system, and keep the domain model intact.\n\nLet me now execute the migration systematically."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12618,"cache_read_input_tokens":71012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12618,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":829},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"aa5b122e-1a96-45cb-ad01-aa7c64a710da"}
