{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012hoYWwthVj2BmHKMmLJCWy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     3→    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     4→\n     5→    <parent>\n     6→        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n     7→        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>\n     8→        <version>3.2.5</version>\n     9→        <relativePath/>\n    10→    </parent>\n    11→\n    12→    <groupId>org.eclipse.ee4j</groupId>\n    13→    <artifactId>cargo-tracker</artifactId>\n    14→    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n    15→    <name>Cargo Tracker</name>\n    16→    <description>Cargo Tracker - Domain Driven Design Example Application</description>\n    17→\n    18→    <properties>\n    19→        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>\n    20→        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    21→        <project.reporting.outputEncoding>UTF-8</project.reporting.outputEncoding>\n    22→    </properties>\n    23→\n    24→    <dependencies>\n    25→        <!-- Spring Boot Starters -->\n    26→        <dependency>\n    27→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    28→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>\n    29→        </dependency>\n    30→        <dependency>\n    31→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    32→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-data-jpa</artifactId>\n    33→        </dependency>\n    34→        <dependency>\n    35→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    36→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>\n    37→        </dependency>\n    38→        <dependency>\n    39→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    40→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-artemis</artifactId>\n    41→        </dependency>\n    42→\n    43→        <!-- Database -->\n    44→        <dependency>\n    45→            <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    46→            <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    47→            <scope>runtime</scope>\n    48→        </dependency>\n    49→\n    50→        <!-- Apache Commons -->\n    51→        <dependency>\n    52→            <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>\n    53→            <artifactId>commons-lang3</artifactId>\n    54→            <version>3.14.0</version>\n    55→        </dependency>\n    56→\n    57→        <!-- Jackson -->\n    58→        <dependency>\n    59→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n    60→            <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>\n    61→        </dependency>\n    62→        <dependency>\n    63→            <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.datatype</groupId>\n    64→            <artifactId>jackson-datatype-jsr310</artifactId>\n    65→        </dependency>\n    66→\n    67→        <!-- JAXB -->\n    68→        <dependency>\n    69→            <groupId>jakarta.xml.bind</groupId>\n    70→            <artifactId>jakarta.xml.bind-api</artifactId>\n    71→            <version>4.0.2</version>\n    72→        </dependency>\n    73→\n    74→        <!-- Test -->\n    75→        <dependency>\n    76→            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    77→            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-test</artifactId>\n    78→            <scope>test</scope>\n    79→        </dependency>\n    80→    </dependencies>\n    81→\n    82→    <build>\n    83→        <plugins>\n    84→            <plugin>\n    85→                <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>\n    86→                <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    87→            </plugin>\n    88→        </plugins>\n    89→    </build>\n    90→</project>\n    91→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"92361733-7dcc-41ae-876f-70f8e466461a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014p6JZRDZ3ZKmP5bL6RcQ2T","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker;\n     2→\n     3→import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\n     4→import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;\n     5→import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.EnableScheduling;\n     6→import org.springframework.jms.annotation.EnableJms;\n     7→\n     8→@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = {\"org.eclipse.cargotracker\", \"org.eclipse.pathfinder\"})\n     9→@EnableScheduling\n    10→@EnableJms\n    11→public class CargoTrackerApplication {\n    12→    public static void main(String[] args) {\n    13→        SpringApplication.run(CargoTrackerApplication.class, args);\n    14→    }\n    15→}\n    16→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"e70f4351-2a62-42d3-b2a5-fa9efb46cd21"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KVwAeYfNPcqWtgWMaQdaWj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.servlet.context-path=/cargo-tracker\n     2→server.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# Datasource\n     5→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:cargotracker;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n     6→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     7→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     8→spring.datasource.password=\n     9→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    10→\n    11→# JPA\n    12→spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n    13→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n    14→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n    15→spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true\n    16→\n    17→# SQL initialization\n    18→spring.sql.init.mode=always\n    19→spring.sql.init.data-locations=classpath:import.sql\n    20→\n    21→# JMS - Embedded ActiveMQ Artemis\n    22→spring.artemis.mode=embedded\n    23→spring.artemis.embedded.enabled=true\n    24→spring.artemis.embedded.queues=CargoHandledQueue,DeliveredCargoQueue,HandlingEventRegistrationAttemptQueue,MisdirectedCargoQueue,RejectedRegistrationAttemptsQueue\n    25→\n    26→# Application settings\n    27→app.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"e69a438a-9ed9-4b56-9689-346b0f359cc6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BxmSbfyRrznGZVdMbhMGZk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl lsof python3-venv python3-full \\\n     6→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     7→\n     8→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     9→\n    10→# Shared browsers path so Chromium is cached once\n    11→ENV PLAYWRIGHT_BROWSERS_PATH=/ms-playwright\n    12→RUN mkdir -p /ms-playwright && chmod 755 /ms-playwright\n    13→\n    14→# create venv and install\n    15→RUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    16→    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python playwright==1.47.0 pytest\n    17→\n    18→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    19→RUN playwright install --with-deps chromium\n    20→\n    21→# Set working directory\n    22→WORKDIR /app\n    23→\n    24→# Copy all the assets\n    25→COPY . .\n    26→\n    27→RUN if [ -f mvnw ]; then chmod +x mvnw; fi && if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    28→\n    29→# Build the application at image build time\n    30→RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests\n    31→\n    32→# Start Spring Boot\n    33→CMD [\"java\", \"-jar\", \"target/cargo-tracker-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\"]\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"f5a7736c-5be3-482f-8f08-17372e2b1f39"}
