{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Mc2JYgxbapDzW5pWBLRvgE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→/** Jakarta REST configuration. */\n     7→@ApplicationPath(\"rest\")\n     8→public class RestConfiguration extends Application {\n     9→}\n    10→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"b1c131a0-408b-4deb-ada5-8ec0d89affc4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0147uAMWpwAzDovGNBR5yvVT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.faces.annotation.FacesConfig;\n     5→\n     6→/** Jakarta Faces configuration. * */\n     7→@FacesConfig\n     8→@ApplicationScoped\n     9→public class FacesConfiguration {\n    10→}\n    11→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"ddf65b1e-e1e4-4042-90f9-1ad654d599aa"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Tw1nMFJmJmPEUbBGfZC9gD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    10→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.flow.FlowScoped;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    16→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Handles booking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    20→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    21→ * interface.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>\n    24→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    25→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    26→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    27→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    28→ */\n    29→@Named\n    30→@FlowScoped(\"booking\")\n    31→public class Booking implements Serializable {\n    32→\n    33→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    34→\n    35→  private static final long MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION = 1; // Journey should be 1 day minimum.\n    36→\n    37→  @Inject\n    38→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    39→  @Inject\n    40→  private FacesContext context;\n    41→\n    42→  private LocalDate today = null;\n    43→  private List<Location> locations;\n    44→\n    45→  private String originUnlocode;\n    46→  private String originName;\n    47→  private String destinationName;\n    48→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    49→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    50→\n    51→  private boolean bookable = false;\n    52→  private long duration = -1;\n    53→\n    54→  @PostConstruct\n    55→  public void init() {\n    56→    today = LocalDate.now();\n    57→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    61→    List<Location> filteredLocations = new ArrayList<>();\n    62→    String locationToRemove = null;\n    63→\n    64→    if (context.getViewRoot().getViewId().endsWith(\"destination.xhtml\")) {\n    65→      // In the destination menu, origin can't be selected.\n    66→      locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    67→    } else { // Vice-versa.\n    68→      if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    69→        locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    70→      }\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    for (Location location : locations) {\n    74→      if (!location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(locationToRemove)) {\n    75→        filteredLocations.add(location);\n    76→      }\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    return filteredLocations;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public String getOriginUnlocode() {\n    83→    return originUnlocode;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public void setOriginUnlocode(String originUnlocode) {\n    87→    this.originUnlocode = originUnlocode;\n    88→    this.originName =\n    89→        locations\n    90→            .stream()\n    91→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(originUnlocode))\n    92→            .findAny()\n    93→            .get()\n    94→            .getName();\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  public String getOriginName() {\n    98→    return originName;\n    99→  }\n   100→\n   101→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n   102→    return destinationUnlocode;\n   103→  }\n   104→\n   105→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n   106→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n   107→    this.destinationName =\n   108→        locations\n   109→            .stream()\n   110→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(destinationUnlocode))\n   111→            .findAny()\n   112→            .get()\n   113→            .getName();\n   114→  }\n   115→\n   116→  public String getDestinationName() {\n   117→    return destinationName;\n   118→  }\n   119→\n   120→  public LocalDate getToday() {\n   121→    return today;\n   122→  }\n   123→\n   124→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n   125→    return arrivalDeadline;\n   126→  }\n   127→\n   128→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n   129→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n   130→  }\n   131→\n   132→  public long getDuration() {\n   133→    return duration;\n   134→  }\n   135→\n   136→  public boolean isBookable() {\n   137→    return bookable;\n   138→  }\n   139→\n   140→  public void deadlineUpdated() {\n   141→    duration = ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(today, arrivalDeadline);\n   142→\n   143→    if (duration >= MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION) {\n   144→      bookable = true;\n   145→    } else {\n   146→      bookable = false;\n   147→    }\n   148→\n   149→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:durationPanel\");\n   150→    PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:bookBtn\");\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  public String register() {\n   154→    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n   155→      bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n   156→    } else {\n   157→      // UI now prevents from selecting same origin/destination\n   158→      FacesMessage message = new FacesMessage(\"Origin and destination cannot be the same.\");\n   159→      message.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n   160→      context.addMessage(null, message);\n   161→      return null;\n   162→    }\n   163→\n   164→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   165→  }\n   166→\n   167→  public String getReturnValue() {\n   168→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   169→  }\n   170→}\n   171→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"37a4a667-a29c-4f35-806c-02778b9ecb84"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NvJydUoQ13ETz1Q1BZdA18","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.RequestScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     6→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n     8→\n     9→/**\n    10→ * Handles viewing cargo details. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    11→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    12→ * tracking user interface.\n    13→ *\n    14→ * <p>\n    15→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    16→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    17→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    18→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    19→ */\n    20→@Named\n    21→@RequestScoped\n    22→public class CargoDetails {\n    23→\n    24→  @Inject\n    25→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    26→\n    27→  private String trackingId;\n    28→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    29→\n    30→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    31→    return trackingId;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    35→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    36→  }\n    37→\n    38→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    39→    return cargo;\n    40→  }\n    41→\n    42→  public void load() {\n    43→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    44→  }\n    45→}\n    46→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"c97cac90-b2bb-432b-9927-6ee7b08bd8da"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DHiVZYLgtYd3RJVvXnMZQm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    15→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    16→ * the tracking user interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>\n    19→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    20→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    21→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    22→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ */\n    24→@Named\n    25→@ViewScoped\n    26→public class ChangeArrivalDeadline implements Serializable {\n    27→\n    28→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    29→\n    30→  @Inject\n    31→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    32→\n    33→  private String trackingId;\n    34→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    35→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    36→\n    37→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    38→    return trackingId;\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    42→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    43→  }\n    44→\n    45→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    46→    return cargo;\n    47→  }\n    48→\n    49→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    50→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    51→  }\n    52→\n    53→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    54→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public void load() {\n    58→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    59→    arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toDate(cargo.getArrivalDeadline());\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public void changeArrivalDeadline() {\n    63→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, arrivalDeadline);\n    64→    PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\");\n    65→  }\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"187c9642-f9ed-4a52-99a0-4b7e4f79cf08"}
