{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01RgqKnjhJGnUTqfFgT1rPfs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles tracking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the public\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>\n    18→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    19→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the public tracking controller. However,\n    20→ * there is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ */\n    23→@Named(\"adminTrack\")\n    24→@ViewScoped\n    25→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    31→\n    32→  private List<String> trackingIds;\n    33→  private String trackingId;\n    34→  private CargoStatus cargo;\n    35→\n    36→  public List<String> getTrackingIds(String query) {\n    37→    return trackingIds;\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    41→    return trackingId;\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    45→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public CargoStatus getCargo() {\n    49→    return this.cargo;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  @PostConstruct\n    53→  public void init() {\n    54→    trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    55→  }\n    56→\n    57→  public void onTrackById() {\n    58→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(this.trackingId);\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"168a3467-58ef-4e5f-aee6-2a190ac57fe5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Lbz7q61fXeTnZP7CJqxpRh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8;\n     4→\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException;\n     7→import java.net.URLEncoder;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    19→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n    20→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * Backing bean for tracking cargo. This interface sits immediately on top of the domain layer,\n    24→ * unlike the booking interface which has a facade and supporting DTOs in between.\n    25→ *\n    26→ * <p>\n    27→ * An adapter class, designed for the tracking use case, is used to wrap the domain model to make it\n    28→ * easier to work with in a web page rendering context. We do not want to apply view rendering\n    29→ * constraints to the design of our domain model and the adapter helps us shield the domain model\n    30→ * classes where needed.\n    31→ *\n    32→ * <p>\n    33→ * In some very simplistic cases, it is fine to not use even an adapter.\n    34→ */\n    35→@Named(\"publicTrack\")\n    36→@ViewScoped\n    37→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    38→\n    39→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    40→\n    41→  @Inject\n    42→  private transient Logger logger;\n    43→\n    44→  @Inject\n    45→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    46→  @Inject\n    47→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    48→  @Inject\n    49→  private ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    50→\n    51→  private String trackingId;\n    52→  private CargoTrackingViewAdapter cargo;\n    53→\n    54→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    55→    return trackingId;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    59→    if (trackingId != null) {\n    60→      trackingId = trackingId.trim();\n    61→    }\n    62→\n    63→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public CargoTrackingViewAdapter getCargo() {\n    67→    return cargo;\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getCargoAsJson() {\n    71→    try {\n    72→      return URLEncoder.encode(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cargo), UTF_8.name());\n    73→    } catch (UnsupportedEncodingException | JsonProcessingException ex) {\n    74→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"URL encoding error.\", ex);\n    75→      return \"\"; // Should never happen.\n    76→    }\n    77→  }\n    78→\n    79→  public void onTrackById() {\n    80→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n    81→\n    82→    if (cargo != null) {\n    83→      List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents =\n    84→          handlingEventRepository\n    85→              .lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(new TrackingId(trackingId))\n    86→              .getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    87→      this.cargo = new CargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo, handlingEvents);\n    88→    } else {\n    89→      this.cargo = null;\n    90→    }\n    91→  }\n    92→}\n    93→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"c9b1a0e5-efeb-451f-a089-b34a878e9cc1"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FFeZwAKY5muvxrs7VJBHfT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.File;\n     4→import java.io.RandomAccessFile;\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.time.format.DateTimeParseException;\n     8→import java.util.Arrays;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→import jakarta.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemReader;\n    12→import jakarta.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    13→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    14→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    15→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    19→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    20→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    22→\n    23→@Dependent\n    24→@Named(\"EventItemReader\")\n    25→public class EventItemReader extends AbstractItemReader {\n    26→\n    27→  private static final String UPLOAD_DIRECTORY = \"upload_directory\";\n    28→\n    29→  @Inject\n    30→  private Logger logger;\n    31→\n    32→  @Inject\n    33→  private JobContext jobContext;\n    34→  private EventFilesCheckpoint checkpoint;\n    35→  private RandomAccessFile currentFile;\n    36→\n    37→  @Override\n    38→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    39→    File uploadDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(UPLOAD_DIRECTORY));\n    40→\n    41→    if (checkpoint == null) {\n    42→      this.checkpoint = new EventFilesCheckpoint();\n    43→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Scanning upload directory: {0}\", uploadDirectory);\n    44→\n    45→      if (!uploadDirectory.exists()) {\n    46→        logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Upload directory does not exist, creating it\");\n    47→        uploadDirectory.mkdirs();\n    48→      } else {\n    49→        this.checkpoint.setFiles(Arrays.asList(uploadDirectory.listFiles()));\n    50→      }\n    51→    } else {\n    52→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Starting from previous checkpoint\");\n    53→      this.checkpoint = (EventFilesCheckpoint) checkpoint;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    File file = this.checkpoint.currentFile();\n    57→\n    58→    if (file == null) {\n    59→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No files to process\");\n    60→      currentFile = null;\n    61→    } else {\n    62→      currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(file, \"r\");\n    63→      logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", file);\n    64→      currentFile.seek(this.checkpoint.getFilePointer());\n    65→    }\n    66→  }\n    67→\n    68→  @Override\n    69→  public Object readItem() throws Exception {\n    70→    if (currentFile != null) {\n    71→      String line = currentFile.readLine();\n    72→\n    73→      if (line != null) {\n    74→        this.checkpoint.setFilePointer(currentFile.getFilePointer());\n    75→        return parseLine(line);\n    76→      } else {\n    77→        logger.log(\n    78→            Level.INFO, \"Finished processing file, deleting: {0}\", this.checkpoint.currentFile());\n    79→        currentFile.close();\n    80→        this.checkpoint.currentFile().delete();\n    81→        File nextFile = this.checkpoint.nextFile();\n    82→\n    83→        if (nextFile == null) {\n    84→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"No more files to process\");\n    85→          return null;\n    86→        } else {\n    87→          currentFile = new RandomAccessFile(nextFile, \"r\");\n    88→          logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Processing file: {0}\", nextFile);\n    89→          return readItem();\n    90→        }\n    91→      }\n    92→    } else {\n    93→      return null;\n    94→    }\n    95→  }\n    96→\n    97→  private Object parseLine(String line) throws EventLineParseException {\n    98→    String[] result = line.split(\",\");\n    99→\n   100→    if (result.length != 5) {\n   101→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Wrong number of data elements\", line);\n   102→    }\n   103→\n   104→    LocalDateTime completionTime = null;\n   105→\n   106→    try {\n   107→      completionTime = DateConverter.toDateTime(result[0]);\n   108→    } catch (DateTimeParseException e) {\n   109→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse completion time\", e, line);\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    TrackingId trackingId = null;\n   113→\n   114→    try {\n   115→      trackingId = new TrackingId(result[1]);\n   116→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   117→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse tracking ID\", e, line);\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    VoyageNumber voyageNumber = null;\n   121→\n   122→    try {\n   123→      if (!result[2].isEmpty()) {\n   124→        voyageNumber = new VoyageNumber(result[2]);\n   125→      }\n   126→    } catch (NullPointerException e) {\n   127→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse voyage number\", e, line);\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    UnLocode unLocode = null;\n   131→\n   132→    try {\n   133→      unLocode = new UnLocode(result[3]);\n   134→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   135→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse UN location code\", e, line);\n   136→    }\n   137→\n   138→    HandlingEvent.Type eventType = null;\n   139→\n   140→    try {\n   141→      eventType = HandlingEvent.Type.valueOf(result[4]);\n   142→    } catch (IllegalArgumentException | NullPointerException e) {\n   143→      throw new EventLineParseException(\"Cannot parse event type\", e, line);\n   144→    }\n   145→\n   146→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n   147→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n   148→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyageNumber, eventType, unLocode);\n   149→\n   150→    return attempt;\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  @Override\n   154→  public Serializable checkpointInfo() throws Exception {\n   155→    return this.checkpoint;\n   156→  }\n   157→}\n   158→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"d2536311-1a63-48d2-8729-9cc354b490c7"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G11raYdeEBRzfhW8HApzfV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.BufferedWriter;\n     4→import java.io.File;\n     5→import java.io.FileWriter;\n     6→import java.io.PrintWriter;\n     7→import java.io.Serializable;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import jakarta.batch.api.chunk.AbstractItemWriter;\n    10→import jakarta.batch.runtime.context.JobContext;\n    11→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n    12→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n    13→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    14→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    18→\n    19→@Dependent\n    20→@Named(\"EventItemWriter\")\n    21→public class EventItemWriter extends AbstractItemWriter {\n    22→\n    23→  private static final String ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY = \"archive_directory\";\n    24→\n    25→  @Inject\n    26→  private JobContext jobContext;\n    27→  @Inject\n    28→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    29→\n    30→  @Override\n    31→  public void open(Serializable checkpoint) throws Exception {\n    32→    File archiveDirectory = new File(jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY));\n    33→\n    34→    if (!archiveDirectory.exists()) {\n    35→      archiveDirectory.mkdirs();\n    36→    }\n    37→  }\n    38→\n    39→  @Override\n    40→  @Transactional\n    41→  public void writeItems(List<Object> items) throws Exception {\n    42→    try (PrintWriter archive =\n    43→        new PrintWriter(\n    44→            new BufferedWriter(\n    45→                new FileWriter(\n    46→                    jobContext.getProperties().getProperty(ARCHIVE_DIRECTORY)\n    47→                        + \"/archive_\"\n    48→                        + jobContext.getJobName()\n    49→                        + \"_\"\n    50→                        + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    51→                        + \".csv\",\n    52→                    true)))) {\n    53→\n    54→      items\n    55→          .stream()\n    56→          .map(item -> (HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt) item)\n    57→          .forEach(\n    58→              attempt -> {\n    59→                applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n    60→                archive.println(\n    61→                    DateConverter.toString(attempt.getRegistrationTime())\n    62→                        + \",\"\n    63→                        + DateConverter.toString(attempt.getCompletionTime())\n    64→                        + \",\"\n    65→                        + attempt.getTrackingId()\n    66→                        + \",\"\n    67→                        + attempt.getVoyageNumber()\n    68→                        + \",\"\n    69→                        + attempt.getUnLocode()\n    70→                        + \",\"\n    71→                        + attempt.getType());\n    72→              });\n    73→    }\n    74→  }\n    75→}\n    76→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"5ebae67b-5808-4153-8375-54861c48d5c9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BiekocyHD6qyQafuPNTZkH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.file;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Date;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     6→import jakarta.batch.api.listener.JobListener;\n     7→import jakarta.enterprise.context.Dependent;\n     8→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     9→import jakarta.inject.Named;\n    10→\n    11→@Dependent\n    12→@Named(\"FileProcessorJobListener\")\n    13→public class FileProcessorJobListener implements JobListener {\n    14→\n    15→  @Inject\n    16→  private Logger logger;\n    17→\n    18→  @Override\n    19→  public void beforeJob() throws Exception {\n    20→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job starting at {0}\", new Date());\n    21→  }\n    22→\n    23→  @Override\n    24→  public void afterJob() throws Exception {\n    25→    logger.log(Level.INFO, \"Handling event file processor batch job completed at {0}\", new Date());\n    26→  }\n    27→}\n    28→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"6965ee42-75e4-4214-999d-b87d13d619e8"}
