{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017517dcMNeffApHtVHd9Lhz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→/**\n     4→ * At the moment, coordinates are effectively a shared DTO in the interface layer. It may be\n     5→ * converted to a domain level concern at some point. *\n     6→ */\n     7→public class Coordinates {\n     8→\n     9→  private final double latitude;\n    10→  private final double longitude;\n    11→\n    12→  public Coordinates(double latitude, double longitude) {\n    13→    this.latitude = latitude;\n    14→    this.longitude = longitude;\n    15→  }\n    16→\n    17→  public double getLatitude() {\n    18→    return latitude;\n    19→  }\n    20→\n    21→  public double getLongitude() {\n    22→    return longitude;\n    23→  }\n    24→}\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"238ce986-f64a-44a8-b51f-0eff44417228"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016Q7UXQg5g67ouHJbz7thcU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces;\n     2→\n     3→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location.UNKNOWN;\n     4→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.CHICAGO;\n     5→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.DALLAS;\n     6→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.GOTHENBURG;\n     7→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HAMBURG;\n     8→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HANGZOU;\n     9→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HELSINKI;\n    10→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.HONGKONG;\n    11→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.MELBOURNE;\n    12→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.NEWYORK;\n    13→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.ROTTERDAM;\n    14→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.SHANGHAI;\n    15→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.STOCKHOLM;\n    16→import static org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.SampleLocations.TOKYO;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Collections;\n    19→import java.util.HashMap;\n    20→import java.util.Map;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    23→\n    24→/**\n    25→ * At the moment, coordinates are produced by a simple factory. It may be converted to a repository\n    26→ * if coordinates become a domain layer concern.\n    27→ */\n    28→public class CoordinatesFactory {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final Map<String, Coordinates> COORDINATES_MAP;\n    31→\n    32→  private CoordinatesFactory() {\n    33→    /* Prevent instantiation. */\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public static Coordinates find(Location location) {\n    37→    return find(location.getUnLocode());\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public static Coordinates find(UnLocode unLocode) {\n    41→    return find(unLocode.getIdString());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public static Coordinates find(String unLocode) {\n    45→    return COORDINATES_MAP.get(unLocode);\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  static {\n    49→    Map<String, Coordinates> map = new HashMap<>();\n    50→\n    51→    // TODO [Clean Code] See if there is a service to get the latitude/longitude data from.\n    52→    map.put(HONGKONG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(22, 114));\n    53→    map.put(MELBOURNE.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-38, 145));\n    54→    map.put(STOCKHOLM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(59, 18));\n    55→    map.put(HELSINKI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(60, 25));\n    56→    map.put(CHICAGO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(42, -88));\n    57→    map.put(TOKYO.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(36, 140));\n    58→    map.put(HAMBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(54, 10));\n    59→    map.put(SHANGHAI.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(31, 121));\n    60→    map.put(ROTTERDAM.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(52, 5));\n    61→    map.put(GOTHENBURG.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(58, 12));\n    62→    map.put(HANGZOU.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(30, 120));\n    63→    map.put(NEWYORK.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(41, -74));\n    64→    map.put(DALLAS.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(33, -97));\n    65→    map.put(UNKNOWN.getUnLocode().getIdString(), new Coordinates(-90, 0)); // The South Pole.\n    66→\n    67→    COORDINATES_MAP = Collections.unmodifiableMap(map);\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"bddf9a9c-1f86-499f-aa84-bece837b3d3d"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ge1kichnmLhNXWZ8aTnCXQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Collections;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Delivery;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.HandlingActivity;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.Coordinates;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.CoordinatesFactory;\n    14→\n    15→/** View adapter for displaying a cargo in a tracking context. */\n    16→public class CargoTrackingViewAdapter {\n    17→\n    18→  private final Cargo cargo;\n    19→  private final List<HandlingEventViewAdapter> events;\n    20→\n    21→  public CargoTrackingViewAdapter(Cargo cargo, List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents) {\n    22→    this.cargo = cargo;\n    23→    this.events = new ArrayList<>(handlingEvents.size());\n    24→\n    25→    handlingEvents.stream().map(HandlingEventViewAdapter::new).forEach(events::add);\n    26→  }\n    27→\n    28→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    29→    return cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString();\n    30→  }\n    31→\n    32→  public String getOriginName() {\n    33→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin().getName();\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  public String getOriginCode() {\n    37→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    38→  }\n    39→\n    40→  public Coordinates getOriginCoordinates() {\n    41→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getOrigin());\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public String getDestinationName() {\n    45→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getName();\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public String getDestinationCode() {\n    49→    return cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  public Coordinates getDestinationCoordinates() {\n    53→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination());\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public String getLastKnownLocationName() {\n    57→    return cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getUnLocode().getIdString().equals(\"XXXXX\")\n    58→        ? \"Unknown\"\n    59→        : cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getName();\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  public String getLastKnownLocationCode() {\n    63→    return cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation().getUnLocode().getIdString();\n    64→  }\n    65→\n    66→  public Coordinates getLastKnownLocationCoordinates() {\n    67→    return CoordinatesFactory.find(cargo.getDelivery().getLastKnownLocation());\n    68→  }\n    69→\n    70→  public String getStatusCode() {\n    71→    if (cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().isEmpty()) {\n    72→      return \"NOT_ROUTED\";\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isUnloadedAtDestination()) {\n    76→      return \"AT_DESTINATION\";\n    77→    }\n    78→\n    79→    if (cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected()) {\n    80→      return \"MISDIRECTED\";\n    81→    }\n    82→\n    83→    return cargo.getDelivery().getTransportStatus().name();\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  /** @return A readable string describing the cargo status. */\n    87→  public String getStatusText() {\n    88→    Delivery delivery = cargo.getDelivery();\n    89→\n    90→    switch (delivery.getTransportStatus()) {\n    91→      case IN_PORT:\n    92→        return \"In port \" + cargo.getRouteSpecification().getDestination().getName();\n    93→      case ONBOARD_CARRIER:\n    94→        return \"Onboard voyage \" + delivery.getCurrentVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString();\n    95→      case CLAIMED:\n    96→        return \"Claimed\";\n    97→      case NOT_RECEIVED:\n    98→        return \"Not received\";\n    99→      case UNKNOWN:\n   100→        return \"Unknown\";\n   101→      default:\n   102→        return \"[Unknown status]\"; // Should never happen.\n   103→    }\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  public boolean isMisdirected() {\n   107→    return cargo.getDelivery().isMisdirected();\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public String getEta() {\n   111→    LocalDateTime eta = cargo.getDelivery().getEstimatedTimeOfArrival();\n   112→\n   113→    if (eta == null) {\n   114→      return \"?\";\n   115→    } else {\n   116→      return DateConverter.toString(eta);\n   117→    }\n   118→  }\n   119→\n   120→  public String getNextExpectedActivity() {\n   121→    HandlingActivity activity = cargo.getDelivery().getNextExpectedActivity();\n   122→\n   123→    if ((activity == null) || (activity.isEmpty())) {\n   124→      return \"\";\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    String text = \"Next expected activity is to \";\n   128→    HandlingEvent.Type type = activity.getType();\n   129→\n   130→    if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.LOAD)) {\n   131→      return text\n   132→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n   133→          + \" cargo onto voyage \"\n   134→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n   135→          + \" in \"\n   136→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   137→    } else if (type.sameValueAs(HandlingEvent.Type.UNLOAD)) {\n   138→      return text\n   139→          + type.name().toLowerCase()\n   140→          + \" cargo off of \"\n   141→          + activity.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber()\n   142→          + \" in \"\n   143→          + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   144→    } else {\n   145→      return text + type.name().toLowerCase() + \" cargo in \" + activity.getLocation().getName();\n   146→    }\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  /** @return An unmodifiable list of handling event view adapters. */\n   150→  public List<HandlingEventViewAdapter> getEvents() {\n   151→    return Collections.unmodifiableList(events);\n   152→  }\n   153→\n   154→  /** Handling event view adapter component. */\n   155→  public class HandlingEventViewAdapter {\n   156→\n   157→    private final HandlingEvent handlingEvent;\n   158→\n   159→    public HandlingEventViewAdapter(HandlingEvent handlingEvent) {\n   160→      this.handlingEvent = handlingEvent;\n   161→    }\n   162→\n   163→    public String getTime() {\n   164→      return DateConverter.toString(handlingEvent.getCompletionTime());\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    public boolean isExpected() {\n   168→      return cargo.getItinerary().isExpected(handlingEvent);\n   169→    }\n   170→\n   171→    public String getDescription() {\n   172→      switch (handlingEvent.getType()) {\n   173→        case LOAD:\n   174→          return \"Loaded onto voyage \"\n   175→              + handlingEvent.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString()\n   176→              + \" in \"\n   177→              + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   178→        case UNLOAD:\n   179→          return \"Unloaded off voyage \"\n   180→              + handlingEvent.getVoyage().getVoyageNumber().getIdString()\n   181→              + \" in \"\n   182→              + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   183→        case RECEIVE:\n   184→          return \"Received in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   185→        case CLAIM:\n   186→          return \"Claimed in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   187→        case CUSTOMS:\n   188→          return \"Cleared customs in \" + handlingEvent.getLocation().getName();\n   189→        default:\n   190→          return \"[Unknown]\";\n   191→      }\n   192→    }\n   193→  }\n   194→}\n   195→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G7yhcnLAQnhjvZ7hMmvvbT","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"c16e1651-a079-4412-9c8a-2513f762c507"}
