{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013S4GvdZMm9KViWan4c1RhW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.UUID;\n     6→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     7→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.NoResultException;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    12→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    13→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.events.cdi.CargoUpdated;\n    15→import org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher;\n    16→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    17→import org.springframework.stereotype.Repository;\n    18→\n    19→@Repository\n    20→public class JpaCargoRepository implements CargoRepository, Serializable {\n    21→\n    22→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    23→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(JpaCargoRepository.class.getName());\n    24→\n    25→    @PersistenceContext\n    26→    private EntityManager entityManager;\n    27→\n    28→    @Autowired\n    29→    private ApplicationEventPublisher eventPublisher;\n    30→\n    31→    @Override\n    32→    public Cargo find(TrackingId trackingId) {\n    33→        Cargo cargo;\n    34→        try {\n    35→            cargo = entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Cargo.findByTrackingId\", Cargo.class)\n    36→                    .setParameter(\"trackingId\", trackingId)\n    37→                    .getSingleResult();\n    38→        } catch (NoResultException e) {\n    39→            logger.log(Level.FINE, \"Find called on non-existant tracking ID.\", e);\n    40→            cargo = null;\n    41→        }\n    42→        return cargo;\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    @Override\n    46→    public void store(Cargo cargo) {\n    47→        cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().forEach(leg -> entityManager.persist(leg));\n    48→        entityManager.persist(cargo);\n    49→        eventPublisher.publishEvent(new CargoUpdated(this, cargo));\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    @Override\n    53→    public TrackingId nextTrackingId() {\n    54→        String random = UUID.randomUUID().toString().toUpperCase();\n    55→        return new TrackingId(random.substring(0, random.indexOf(\"-\")));\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    @Override\n    59→    public List<Cargo> findAll() {\n    60→        return entityManager.createQuery(\"Select c from Cargo c\", Cargo.class).getResultList();\n    61→    }\n    62→}\n    63→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"db705187-897d-4d2e-a896-491cf45b4910"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L6dfY3rbQPY5JwuDHH2h3W","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface CargoRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Cargo find(TrackingId trackingId);\n     8→\n     9→  void store(Cargo cargo);\n    10→\n    11→  TrackingId nextTrackingId();\n    12→\n    13→  List<Cargo> findAll();\n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"fc131974-8236-4ec8-926b-69dba90e04a5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HGmJbamPEFxhF91GApKKLy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→\n     5→public interface LocationRepository {\n     6→\n     7→  Location find(UnLocode unLocode);\n     8→\n     9→  List<Location> findAll();\n    10→\n    11→}\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"92497b39-d14e-4f58-9e8d-88c0ea3a8544"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JgLiRfJ3KnA4iJstG62CaE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.mobile;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.util.stream.Collectors.toMap;\n     4→\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.time.LocalDateTime;\n     7→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     8→import java.util.Arrays;\n     9→import java.util.Collections;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→import java.util.Map;\n    12→import java.util.function.Function;\n    13→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    14→// import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    15→// import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    16→// import jakarta.faces.model.SelectItem;\n    17→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n    18→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    19→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    20→import org.springframework.data.domain.Sort;\n    21→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.ApplicationEvents;\n    22→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n    23→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    24→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    25→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TransportStatus;\n    26→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    27→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.Location;\n    28→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.location.UnLocode;\n    29→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.Voyage;\n    30→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.voyage.VoyageNumber;\n    31→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa.JpaCargoRepository;\n    32→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa.JpaLocationRepository;\n    33→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.infrastructure.persistence.jpa.JpaVoyageRepository;\n    34→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.handling.HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt;\n    35→// import org.primefaces.event.FlowEvent;\n    36→// import io.quarkus.panache.common.Sort;\n    37→\n    38→/**\n    39→ * NOTE: JSF/PrimeFaces and Quarkus Panache-specific functionality has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    40→ * This class structure is preserved but JSF features are disabled.\n    41→ */\n    42→@Component(\"eventLogger\")\n    43→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    44→public class EventLogger implements Serializable {\n    45→\n    46→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    47→\n    48→  @Autowired\n    49→  private JpaCargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    50→  @Autowired\n    51→  private JpaLocationRepository locationRepository;\n    52→  @Autowired\n    53→  private JpaVoyageRepository voyageRepository;\n    54→  @Autowired\n    55→  private ApplicationEvents applicationEvents;\n    56→  // @Inject\n    57→  // private FacesContext context; // JSF-specific - commented out\n    58→\n    59→  // Using simple list instead of JSF SelectItem\n    60→  private List<Object> trackingIds; // Changed from List<SelectItem>\n    61→  private List<Object> locations;   // Changed from List<SelectItem>\n    62→  private List<Object> voyages;     // Changed from List<SelectItem>\n    63→\n    64→  private String trackingId;\n    65→  private String location;\n    66→  private HandlingEvent.Type eventType;\n    67→  private String voyageNumber;\n    68→  private LocalDateTime completionTime;\n    69→\n    70→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    71→    return trackingId;\n    72→  }\n    73→\n    74→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    75→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    76→  }\n    77→\n    78→  public List<Object> getTrackingIds() {\n    79→    return trackingIds;\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public String getLocation() {\n    83→    return location;\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public void setLocation(String location) {\n    87→    this.location = location;\n    88→  }\n    89→\n    90→  public List<Object> getLocations() {\n    91→    return locations;\n    92→  }\n    93→\n    94→  // Move this to a separate utility if it is used in other parts of the UI.\n    95→  public Map<HandlingEvent.Type, HandlingEvent.Type> getEventTypes() {\n    96→    return Collections.unmodifiableMap(\n    97→        Arrays.asList(HandlingEvent.Type.values())\n    98→            .stream()\n    99→            .collect(toMap(Function.identity(), Function.identity())));\n   100→  }\n   101→\n   102→  public HandlingEvent.Type getEventType() {\n   103→    return eventType;\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  public void setEventType(HandlingEvent.Type eventType) {\n   107→    this.eventType = eventType;\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public String getVoyageNumber() {\n   111→    return voyageNumber;\n   112→  }\n   113→\n   114→  public void setVoyageNumber(String voyageNumber) {\n   115→    this.voyageNumber = voyageNumber;\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  public List<Object> getVoyages() {\n   119→    return voyages;\n   120→  }\n   121→\n   122→  public LocalDateTime getCompletionTime() {\n   123→    return completionTime;\n   124→  }\n   125→\n   126→  public void setCompletionTime(LocalDateTime completionTime) {\n   127→    this.completionTime = completionTime;\n   128→  }\n   129→\n   130→  public String getCompletionTimeValue() {\n   131→    return DateConverter.toString(completionTime);\n   132→  }\n   133→\n   134→  public String getCompletionTimePattern() {\n   135→    return DateConverter.DATE_TIME_FORMAT;\n   136→  }\n   137→\n   138→  @PostConstruct\n   139→  public void init() {\n   140→    // Using Spring Data JPA methods instead of Panache\n   141→    List<Cargo> cargos = cargoRepository.findAll();\n   142→\n   143→    trackingIds = new ArrayList<>(cargos.size());\n   144→\n   145→    // List only routed cargo that is not claimed yet.\n   146→    // Note: SelectItem replaced with simple String objects for non-JSF usage\n   147→    cargos\n   148→        .stream()\n   149→        .filter(\n   150→            cargo -> !cargo.getItinerary().getLegs().isEmpty()\n   151→                && !(cargo\n   152→                    .getDelivery()\n   153→                    .getTransportStatus()\n   154→                    .sameValueAs(TransportStatus.CLAIMED)))\n   155→        .map(cargo -> cargo.getTrackingId().getIdString())\n   156→        .forEachOrdered(trackingId -> trackingIds.add(trackingId)); // Changed: no SelectItem wrapper\n   157→\n   158→    List<Location> locations = locationRepository.findAll();\n   159→\n   160→    this.locations = new ArrayList<>(locations.size());\n   161→\n   162→    locations.forEach(\n   163→        location -> {\n   164→          String locationCode = location.getUnLocode().getIdString();\n   165→          this.locations.add(locationCode); // Changed: no SelectItem wrapper\n   166→        });\n   167→\n   168→    // Using Spring Data Sort instead of Panache Sort\n   169→    List<Voyage> voyages = voyageRepository.findAll(Sort.by(\"voyageNumber\"));\n   170→\n   171→    this.voyages = new ArrayList<>(voyages.size());\n   172→\n   173→    voyages.forEach(\n   174→        voyage -> this.voyages.add(voyage.getVoyageNumber().getIdString())); // Changed: no SelectItem wrapper\n   175→  }\n   176→\n   177→  public String onFlowProcess(Object event) {\n   178→    // JSF FlowEvent functionality commented out\n   179→    // if (!validate(event.getOldStep())) {\n   180→    //   return event.getOldStep();\n   181→    // }\n   182→    //\n   183→    // if (\"dateTab\".equals(event.getNewStep())) {\n   184→    //   completionTime = LocalDateTime.now();\n   185→    // }\n   186→    //\n   187→    // return event.getNewStep();\n   188→    return null;\n   189→  }\n   190→\n   191→  private boolean validate(final String step) {\n   192→    // JSF validation commented out\n   193→    // if (\"voyageTab\".equals(step) && eventType.requiresVoyage() && voyageNumber == null) {\n   194→    //   FacesMessage message =\n   195→    //       new FacesMessage(\n   196→    //           FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR,\n   197→    //           \"When a cargo is LOADed or UNLOADed a Voyage should be selected, please fix errors to continue.\",\n   198→    //           \"\");\n   199→    //   context.addMessage(null, message);\n   200→    //   return false;\n   201→    // }\n   202→\n   203→    return true;\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→  public void submit() {\n   207→    VoyageNumber voyage;\n   208→\n   209→    TrackingId trackingId = new TrackingId(this.trackingId);\n   210→    UnLocode location = new UnLocode(this.location);\n   211→\n   212→    if (eventType.requiresVoyage()) {\n   213→      voyage = new VoyageNumber(voyageNumber);\n   214→    } else {\n   215→      voyage = null;\n   216→    }\n   217→\n   218→    HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt attempt =\n   219→        new HandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(\n   220→            LocalDateTime.now(), completionTime, trackingId, voyage, eventType, location);\n   221→\n   222→    applicationEvents.receivedHandlingEventRegistrationAttempt(attempt);\n   223→\n   224→    // FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null, new FacesMessage(\"Event submitted\", \"\"));\n   225→    // JSF FacesMessage commented out\n   226→  }\n   227→}\n   228→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"88071f16-625a-4ba1-b399-d8e9abf4ae0c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01J2VUokPZ3AJmK6TzJ1UyXt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see an issue with EventLogger - it calls `voyageRepository.findAll(Sort.by(\"voyageNumber\"))` but JpaVoyageRepository doesn't have a `findAll(Sort)` method. Let me fix this and also check the VoyageRepository interface. Also, the `store` method in JpaCargoRepository uses `entityManager.persist()` but for updates it should use `merge`. Let me fix these issues:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5133,"cache_read_input_tokens":106160,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5133,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":453},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"d4f3bf62-608f-4577-8a40-06b24a31ff4a"}
