) e;\n    42→    //\n    43→    // logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Problem parsing event file line\", parseException);\n    44→    //\n    45→    // try (PrintWriter failed =\n    46→    //     new PrintWriter(\n    47→    //         new BufferedWriter(\n    48→    //             new FileWriter(\n    49→    //                 new File(\n    50→    //                     failedDirectory,\n    51→    //                     \"failed_\"\n    52→    //                         + jobContext.getJobName()\n    53→    //                         + \"_\"\n    54→    //                         + jobContext.getInstanceId()\n    55→    //                         + \".csv\"),\n    56→    //                 true)))) {\n    57→    //   failed.println(parseException.getLine());\n    58→    // }\n    59→  }\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"dde56fae-7c63-4e16-afd0-4eb056fa6151"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016JQ5RpiVy3khfShmDraXnF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.tracking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import static java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets.UTF_8;\n     4→\n     5→import java.io.Serializable;\n     6→import java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException;\n     7→import java.net.URLEncoder;\n     8→import java.util.List;\n     9→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    10→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    11→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n    12→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    13→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.Cargo;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.CargoRepository;\n    16→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.cargo.TrackingId;\n    17→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEvent;\n    18→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.domain.model.handling.HandlingEventRepository;\n    19→import com.fasterxml.jackson.core.JsonProcessingException;\n    20→import com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper;\n    21→\n    22→/**\n    23→ * Backing bean for tracking cargo. This interface sits immediately on top of the domain layer,\n    24→ * unlike the booking interface which has a facade and supporting DTOs in between.\n    25→ *\n    26→ * <p>\n    27→ * An adapter class, designed for the tracking use case, is used to wrap the domain model to make it\n    28→ * easier to work with in a web page rendering context. We do not want to apply view rendering\n    29→ * constraints to the design of our domain model and the adapter helps us shield the domain model\n    30→ * classes where needed.\n    31→ *\n    32→ * <p>\n    33→ * In some very simplistic cases, it is fine to not use even an adapter.\n    34→ *\n    35→ * <p>\n    36→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality (ViewScoped) has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    37→ */\n    38→@Component(\"publicTrack\")\n    39→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    40→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    41→\n    42→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    43→\n    44→  @Autowired\n    45→  private transient Logger logger;\n    46→\n    47→  @Autowired\n    48→  private CargoRepository cargoRepository;\n    49→  @Autowired\n    50→  private HandlingEventRepository handlingEventRepository;\n    51→  @Autowired\n    52→  private ObjectMapper objectMapper;\n    53→\n    54→  private String trackingId;\n    55→  private CargoTrackingViewAdapter cargo;\n    56→\n    57→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    58→    return trackingId;\n    59→  }\n    60→\n    61→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    62→    if (trackingId != null) {\n    63→      trackingId = trackingId.trim();\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    67→  }\n    68→\n    69→  public CargoTrackingViewAdapter getCargo() {\n    70→    return cargo;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public String getCargoAsJson() {\n    74→    try {\n    75→      return URLEncoder.encode(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(cargo), UTF_8.name());\n    76→    } catch (UnsupportedEncodingException | JsonProcessingException ex) {\n    77→      logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"URL encoding error.\", ex);\n    78→      return \"\"; // Should never happen.\n    79→    }\n    80→  }\n    81→\n    82→  public void onTrackById() {\n    83→    Cargo cargo = cargoRepository.find(new TrackingId(trackingId));\n    84→\n    85→    if (cargo != null) {\n    86→      List<HandlingEvent> handlingEvents =\n    87→          handlingEventRepository\n    88→              .lookupHandlingHistoryOfCargo(new TrackingId(trackingId))\n    89→              .getDistinctEventsByCompletionTime();\n    90→      this.cargo = new CargoTrackingViewAdapter(cargo, handlingEvents);\n    91→    } else {\n    92→      this.cargo = null;\n    93→    }\n    94→  }\n    95→}\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"af22ace8-1252-4e43-a6ff-a15834919272"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F79nYXD2FNnnjE6oP5bgjR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.temporal.ChronoUnit;\n     6→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     7→import java.util.List;\n     8→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→// import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    10→// import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    11→// import jakarta.faces.flow.FlowScoped;\n    12→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n    13→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n    14→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    15→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    16→// import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Handles booking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be rewritten\n    20→ * as a thick client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the tracking user\n    21→ * interface.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>\n    24→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    25→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    26→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    27→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    28→ *\n    29→ * <p>\n    30→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    31→ * This backing bean structure is preserved but JSF features are disabled.\n    32→ */\n    33→@Component(\"booking\")\n    34→// @FlowScoped(\"booking\") // JSF flow scope - not applicable in Spring\n    35→public class Booking implements Serializable {\n    36→\n    37→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    38→\n    39→  private static final long MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION = 1; // Journey should be 1 day minimum.\n    40→\n    41→  @Autowired\n    42→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    43→\n    44→  // @Inject\n    45→  // private FacesContext context; // JSF-specific - commented out\n    46→\n    47→  private LocalDate today = null;\n    48→  private List<Location> locations;\n    49→\n    50→  private String originUnlocode;\n    51→  private String originName;\n    52→  private String destinationName;\n    53→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    54→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    55→\n    56→  private boolean bookable = false;\n    57→  private long duration = -1;\n    58→\n    59→  @PostConstruct\n    60→  public void init() {\n    61→    today = LocalDate.now();\n    62→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    66→    List<Location> filteredLocations = new ArrayList<>();\n    67→    String locationToRemove = null;\n    68→\n    69→    // JSF-specific view logic commented out\n    70→    // if (context.getViewRoot().getViewId().endsWith(\"destination.xhtml\")) {\n    71→    //   // In the destination menu, origin can't be selected.\n    72→    //   locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    73→    // } else { // Vice-versa.\n    74→    //   if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    75→    //     locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    76→    //   }\n    77→    // }\n    78→\n    79→    // For now, return all locations (REST API usage)\n    80→    if (destinationUnlocode != null) {\n    81→      locationToRemove = destinationUnlocode;\n    82→    } else if (originUnlocode != null) {\n    83→      locationToRemove = originUnlocode;\n    84→    }\n    85→\n    86→    for (Location location : locations) {\n    87→      if (locationToRemove == null || !location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(locationToRemove)) {\n    88→        filteredLocations.add(location);\n    89→      }\n    90→    }\n    91→\n    92→    return filteredLocations;\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  public String getOriginUnlocode() {\n    96→    return originUnlocode;\n    97→  }\n    98→\n    99→  public void setOriginUnlocode(String originUnlocode) {\n   100→    this.originUnlocode = originUnlocode;\n   101→    this.originName =\n   102→        locations\n   103→            .stream()\n   104→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(originUnlocode))\n   105→            .findAny()\n   106→            .get()\n   107→            .getName();\n   108→  }\n   109→\n   110→  public String getOriginName() {\n   111→    return originName;\n   112→  }\n   113→\n   114→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n   115→    return destinationUnlocode;\n   116→  }\n   117→\n   118→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n   119→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n   120→    this.destinationName =\n   121→        locations\n   122→            .stream()\n   123→            .filter(location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(destinationUnlocode))\n   124→            .findAny()\n   125→            .get()\n   126→            .getName();\n   127→  }\n   128→\n   129→  public String getDestinationName() {\n   130→    return destinationName;\n   131→  }\n   132→\n   133→  public LocalDate getToday() {\n   134→    return today;\n   135→  }\n   136→\n   137→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n   138→    return arrivalDeadline;\n   139→  }\n   140→\n   141→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n   142→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n   143→  }\n   144→\n   145→  public long getDuration() {\n   146→    return duration;\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  public boolean isBookable() {\n   150→    return bookable;\n   151→  }\n   152→\n   153→  public void deadlineUpdated() {\n   154→    duration = ChronoUnit.DAYS.between(today, arrivalDeadline);\n   155→\n   156→    if (duration >= MIN_JOURNEY_DURATION) {\n   157→      bookable = true;\n   158→    } else {\n   159→      bookable = false;\n   160→    }\n   161→\n   162→    // PrimeFaces AJAX calls commented out (JSF-specific)\n   163→    // PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:durationPanel\");\n   164→    // PrimeFaces.current().ajax().update(\"dateForm:bookBtn\");\n   165→  }\n   166→\n   167→  public String register() {\n   168→    if (!originUnlocode.equals(destinationUnlocode)) {\n   169→      bookingServiceFacade.bookNewCargo(originUnlocode, destinationUnlocode, arrivalDeadline);\n   170→    } else {\n   171→      // UI now prevents from selecting same origin/destination\n   172→      // FacesMessage message = new FacesMessage(\"Origin and destination cannot be the same.\");\n   173→      // message.setSeverity(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n   174→      // context.addMessage(null, message);\n   175→      return null;\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   179→  }\n   180→\n   181→  public String getReturnValue() {\n   182→    return \"/admin/dashboard.xhtml\";\n   183→  }\n   184→}\n   185→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"337c6b22-b356-4e0e-96d5-11fc08cbec3e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XL83n6fQ7RMPZ9Ra3PUUrf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     6→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     8→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoStatus;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles tracking cargo. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the public\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>\n    18→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    19→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the public tracking controller. However,\n    20→ * there is never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two\n    21→ * polarized ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>\n    24→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality (ViewScoped) has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    25→ */\n    26→@Component(\"adminTrack\")\n    27→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    28→public class Track implements Serializable {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    31→\n    32→  @Autowired\n    33→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    34→\n    35→  private List<String> trackingIds;\n    36→  private String trackingId;\n    37→  private CargoStatus cargo;\n    38→\n    39→  public List<String> getTrackingIds(String query) {\n    40→    return trackingIds;\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    44→    return trackingId;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    48→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public CargoStatus getCargo() {\n    52→    return this.cargo;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  @PostConstruct\n    56→  public void init() {\n    57→    trackingIds = bookingServiceFacade.listAllTrackingIds();\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  public void onTrackById() {\n    61→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForTracking(this.trackingId);\n    62→  }\n    63→}\n    64→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"730393d2-0d97-45b9-8c36-f01b09171fea"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012yaUbMivUWaoHiSaPZ6kto","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.application.util.DateConverter;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→// import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    12→\n    13→/**\n    14→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    15→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    16→ * the tracking user interface.\n    17→ *\n    18→ * <p>\n    19→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    20→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    21→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    22→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    23→ *\n    24→ * <p>\n    25→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality (ViewScoped, PrimeFaces) has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    26→ */\n    27→@Component(\"changeArrivalDeadline\")\n    28→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    29→public class ChangeArrivalDeadline implements Serializable {\n    30→\n    31→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    32→\n    33→  @Autowired\n    34→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    35→\n    36→  private String trackingId;\n    37→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    38→  private LocalDate arrivalDeadline;\n    39→\n    40→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    41→    return trackingId;\n    42→  }\n    43→\n    44→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    45→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    46→  }\n    47→\n    48→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    49→    return cargo;\n    50→  }\n    51→\n    52→  public LocalDate getArrivalDeadline() {\n    53→    return arrivalDeadline;\n    54→  }\n    55→\n    56→  public void setArrivalDeadline(LocalDate arrivalDeadline) {\n    57→    this.arrivalDeadline = arrivalDeadline;\n    58→  }\n    59→\n    60→  public void load() {\n    61→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    62→    arrivalDeadline = DateConverter.toDate(cargo.getArrivalDeadline());\n    63→  }\n    64→\n    65→  public void changeArrivalDeadline() {\n    66→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDeadline(trackingId, arrivalDeadline);\n    67→    // PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\"); // JSF-specific - commented out\n    68→  }\n    69→}\n    70→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"8a5c7e13-0956-4208-ba3f-717602a44727"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TFKrN53pFfkTC3n9mPbC6q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.stream.Collectors;\n     6→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     7→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     8→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    11→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.Location;\n    12→// import org.primefaces.PrimeFaces;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Handles changing the cargo destination. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could\n    16→ * easily be rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike\n    17→ * the tracking user interface.\n    18→ *\n    19→ * <p>\n    20→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    21→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    22→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    23→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    24→ *\n    25→ * <p>\n    26→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality (ViewScoped, PrimeFaces) has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    27→ */\n    28→@Component(\"changeDestination\")\n    29→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    30→public class ChangeDestination implements Serializable {\n    31→\n    32→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    33→\n    34→  @Autowired\n    35→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    36→\n    37→  private String trackingId;\n    38→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    39→  private List<Location> locations;\n    40→  private String destinationUnlocode;\n    41→\n    42→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    43→    return trackingId;\n    44→  }\n    45→\n    46→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    47→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    48→  }\n    49→\n    50→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    51→    return cargo;\n    52→  }\n    53→\n    54→  public List<Location> getLocations() {\n    55→    return locations;\n    56→  }\n    57→\n    58→  public List<Location> getPotentialDestinations() {\n    59→    // Potential destination = All Locations - Origin - Current Destination\n    60→    List<Location> destinationsToRemove =\n    61→        locations\n    62→            .stream()\n    63→            .filter(\n    64→                location -> location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getOriginCode())\n    65→                    || location.getUnLocode().equalsIgnoreCase(cargo.getFinalDestinationCode()))\n    66→            .collect(Collectors.toList());\n    67→\n    68→    locations.removeAll(destinationsToRemove);\n    69→\n    70→    return locations;\n    71→  }\n    72→\n    73→  public String getDestinationUnlocode() {\n    74→    return destinationUnlocode;\n    75→  }\n    76→\n    77→  public void setDestinationUnlocode(String destinationUnlocode) {\n    78→    this.destinationUnlocode = destinationUnlocode;\n    79→  }\n    80→\n    81→  public void load() {\n    82→    locations = bookingServiceFacade.listShippingLocations();\n    83→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  public void changeDestination() {\n    87→    bookingServiceFacade.changeDestination(trackingId, destinationUnlocode);\n    88→    // PrimeFaces.current().dialog().closeDynamic(\"DONE\"); // JSF-specific - commented out\n    89→    // RequestContext.getCurrentInstance().closeDialog(\"DONE\"); // JSF-specific - commented out\n    90→  }\n    91→}\n    92→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"b970350c-1b38-414f-94dc-2fc008fe5337"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QKtkZPobz7gBuDDcH6SGze","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.io.Serializable;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→// import jakarta.faces.view.ViewScoped;\n     6→import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Autowired;\n     7→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     8→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.BookingServiceFacade;\n     9→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.CargoRoute;\n    10→import org.eclipse.cargotracker.interfaces.booking.facade.dto.RouteCandidate;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Handles itinerary selection. Operates against a dedicated service facade, and could easily be\n    14→ * rewritten as a thick Swing client. Completely separated from the domain layer, unlike the\n    15→ * tracking user interface.\n    16→ *\n    17→ * <p>\n    18→ * In order to successfully keep the domain model shielded from user interface considerations, this\n    19→ * approach is generally preferred to the one taken in the tracking controller. However, there is\n    20→ * never any one perfect solution for all situations, so we've chosen to demonstrate two polarized\n    21→ * ways to build user interfaces.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * <p>\n    24→ * NOTE: JSF-specific functionality (ViewScoped) has been commented out for Spring Boot migration.\n    25→ */\n    26→@Component(\"itinerarySelection\")\n    27→// @ViewScoped // JSF view scope - commented out for Spring\n    28→public class ItinerarySelection implements Serializable {\n    29→\n    30→  private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    31→\n    32→  @Autowired\n    33→  private BookingServiceFacade bookingServiceFacade;\n    34→\n    35→  List<RouteCandidate> routeCandidates;\n    36→  private String trackingId;\n    37→  private CargoRoute cargo;\n    38→\n    39→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCandidates() {\n    40→    return routeCandidates;\n    41→  }\n    42→\n    43→  public String getTrackingId() {\n    44→    return trackingId;\n    45→  }\n    46→\n    47→  public void setTrackingId(String trackingId) {\n    48→    this.trackingId = trackingId;\n    49→  }\n    50→\n    51→  public CargoRoute getCargo() {\n    52→    return cargo;\n    53→  }\n    54→\n    55→  public List<RouteCandidate> getRouteCanditates() {\n    56→    return routeCandidates;\n    57→  }\n    58→\n    59→  public void load() {\n    60→    cargo = bookingServiceFacade.loadCargoForRouting(trackingId);\n    61→    routeCandidates = bookingServiceFacade.requestPossibleRoutesForCargo(trackingId);\n    62→  }\n    63→\n    64→  public String assignItinerary(int routeIndex) {\n    65→    RouteCandidate route = routeCandidates.get(routeIndex);\n    66→    bookingServiceFacade.assignCargoToRoute(trackingId, route);\n    67→\n    68→    return \"show.html?faces-redirect=true&trackingId=\" + trackingId;\n    69→  }\n    70→}\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CLaJYLpEvBtbPJnGcBG5RL","session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"e9806110-d8a7-4850-b06b-2cb5b2f1e9e2"}
