{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BjvvNuZqDcNf9dKYZKqyEh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→server.servlet.context-path=/cargo-tracker\n     2→server.port=8080\n     3→\n     4→# Datasource\n     5→spring.datasource.url=jdbc:h2:mem:cargotracker;DB_CLOSE_DELAY=-1;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n     6→spring.datasource.driverClassName=org.h2.Driver\n     7→spring.datasource.username=sa\n     8→spring.datasource.password=\n     9→spring.h2.console.enabled=true\n    10→\n    11→# JPA\n    12→spring.jpa.database-platform=org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect\n    13→spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=create-drop\n    14→spring.jpa.show-sql=true\n    15→spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true\n    16→\n    17→# SQL initialization\n    18→spring.sql.init.mode=always\n    19→spring.sql.init.data-locations=classpath:import.sql\n    20→\n    21→# Messaging - using Spring ApplicationEvents (no JMS broker needed)\n    22→\n    23→# Application settings\n    24→app.configuration.GraphTraversalUrl=http://localhost:8080/cargo-tracker/rest/graph-traversal/shortest-path\n    25→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"d3e882d8-da93-4999-8923-b661a268f952"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_017dBVYkxSxXYJ2ePW2KutBR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem: `spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true` should allow SQL init AFTER Hibernate creates tables, but it seems the import.sql path is being resolved differently. The simplest fix is to use Hibernate's built-in import.sql mechanism - Hibernate automatically looks for `import.sql` on the classpath when `ddl-auto` is `create` or `create-drop`. I just need to remove the Spring SQL init settings and rename the file to be in the right spot:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":901,"cache_read_input_tokens":133933,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":901,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":223},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"726ac45c-03cf-4dc6-9fff-d69b80f6c98b","uuid":"f1a00ab1-ab1d-4a44-9046-21b52a9e4815"}
